Rating: 3
This is so delicious! I've made it twice and both times it has been excellent. The chicken is so tender and flavorful. The shrimp is good too, but you could leave it out if you didn't have any. Everybody's taste buds are different, but I'm not sure where the "bland" comments came from....this dish is far from bland. Matter of fact, I doubled the sauce this time while keeping the original amount of cayenne, and it still had plenty of flavor. Used 1C whipping cream and 1C half and half, and once mixed with the pasta it was fine. Thanks to the lady who suggested one egg - I hate to waste. Might I also suggest cutting the bread crumb mixture in half....you'll never use the whole two cups, I threw a bunch away. This ain't diet food, but it is wonderful and does remind me of a meal in a New Orleans restaurant. Such fond memories.

