Rating: 4
This is a fantastic recipe. There are just a few extra steps I add. First, I heavily season the shrimp with salt and pepper before putting them in the pan. Also, after browning the chicken, I deglaze the pan with some of the white wine so it picks up the bits of chicken stuck to the pan. Leave these in the pan, add the oil, then cook the shrimp. It really fuses the flavors nicely.

